Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 33
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 33

Non‑Adversarial Format — Make It Easy to Say Yes

⚖️ Core Message

Write like you’re helping the judge do the right thing quickly.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Parallel Paths: Primary relief and a tight alternative the court can grant today.
2. Neutral Tone: Facts first, then law; avoid adjectives and adverbs.
3. Short Orders: Attach a one‑page order the court can sign without edits.
4. Friction Audit: Remove any step you wouldn’t want to do as a busy judge.
📝 Assignment

Rewrite a motion intro into a non‑adversarial paragraph that names the test, the record cite, and the narrow relief.
✅ Model Response

INTRO (sample)

Plaintiff seeks interim relief under Winter: success, harm, equities, public interest.

Record: Ex. A (delivery), Dkt 18 (docketing). Relief: a 20‑minute hearing this week.

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Help the court help you.
🎨 Visual Concept

A green check hovering over a one‑page order.
